Vert.x/WebClient test scaffold and does not need Docker or extra required dependencies, but it still pulls Netty 4.2.x and should carry forward the Java 25 native runtime unsafe-access system properties already needed for 5.0.0.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"For native-image runtime tests on JDK 25/current-defaults, set the same runtime system properties used for 5.0.0: -Dsun.misc.unsafe.memory.access=allow and -Dio.netty.tryReflectionSetAccessible=true. The existing condition limited to libraryVersion == '5.0.0' should be extended to cover 5.0.1 or the affected Vert.x 5.0.x/Netty 4.2.x versions. Core coverage can use an in-process Vert.x HttpServer on localhost; no external service is required. Only add io.vertx:vertx-auth-oauth2 if tests intentionally exercise OAuth2WebClient, because that API depends on an optional dependency.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"If the generated tests exercise OAuth2WebClient without adding the optional vertx-auth-oauth2 dependency, compilation may fail; this is avoidable by focusing coverage on the core WebClient, CachingWebClient, WebClientSession, BodyCodec, forms, multipart, redirects, cookies, and local HTTP interactions.\",\n    \"Local Gradle/native-image verification remains authoritative because the observed failure is runtime-specific to JDK 25 native execution.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0105583f6f089a05016a40f59a2cb48197a87bc643b6cc2669\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1502, "output": 445, "cacheRead": 26112, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 28059, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782642071396, "responseId": "resp_0105583f6f089a05016a40f597e40081978eda5689b3591a0a"}}
